<p>Famously known as the K beauty routine, here are the 8 Korean skin care regimen for your personal beauty secrets.</p>

<h1 id="step-1-cleanser">Step 1: Cleanser</h1>
<p>Properly wash your face with only water in the morning. Now this might be skeptical, but washing your face only with water will clean the impurities settled in your face at night and hydrates it too.</p>

<h1 id="step-2-toner">Step 2: Toner</h1>
<p>Now if youâ€™re new to toner, toner helps balance the pH level of the skin, which ideally should be slightly acidic â€“ at about 5.5. It hydrates the skin along with prepping your skin for further products that youâ€™ll be applying.
<img src="/assets/images/aloe-toner.png" alt="Jeju Aloe Aqua Toner" title="Jeju Aloe Aqua Toner " /></p>

<h1 id="step-3-essence">Step 3: Essence</h1>
<p>Essence is a mixture of toner and serum. Essence help in hydrating your skin, increase cellular turnover and provide a youthful brightness in your skin.</p>

<p><img src="/assets/images/Snail-essence.png" alt="Snail Bee high content essence " title="Snail Bee high content essence " /></p>

<h1 id="step-4-ampoule">Step 4: Ampoule</h1>
<p>Ampoule is quite similar to serum but are packed with <a href="https://sheenycare.com/active-ingredients-for-skin-care/">active ingredients</a> that are used to target specific skin concern. They are used for a specific period of time, especially when your skin needs help.</p>

<p><img src="/assets/images/ampoule.png" alt="Hydrium Triple Hyaluronic Moisture Ampoule" title="Hydrium Triple Hyaluronic Moisture Ampoule" /></p>

<h1 id="step-5-serum">Step 5: Serum</h1>
<p>Serum are packed with several active ingredients together. These serums are packed with a balanced concerntration of different active ingredients. They are specifically used for aging, skin dehydration, hyperpigmentation, dark spots etc</p>

<p><img src="/assets/images/serum.png" alt="Bright Potion Probiotic Power Serum" title="Bright Potion Probiotic Power Serum" /></p>

<h1 id="step-6-eye-cream">Step 6: Eye Cream</h1>
<p>The skin around the eye is thinnest as there are no <a href="https://www.google.com/search?channel=fs&amp;client=ubuntu&amp;q=sebaceous+glands" rel="nofollow" target="_blank"> sebacious gland</a> to produce natural oil. So a simple eye cream is used to hydrate and protect this part of the face.</p>

<p><img src="/assets/images/eyecream.png" alt="Starting Treatment Eye Cream " title="Starting Treatment Eye Cream " /></p>

<h1 id="step-7-moisturiser">Step 7: Moisturiser</h1>
<p>Every skin care routine has one, and so does Korean skin care routine. Apply a generous amount of moisturiser to hydrate your skin.</p>

<p><img src="/assets/images/moisturiser.png" alt="Water Drop Hydrating Moisturizer" title="Water Drop Hydrating Moisturizer" /></p>

<h1 id="step-8-sunscreen">Step 8: Sunscreen</h1>
<p>Protecting the skin from the UV rays is a must. Sunscreen is a mandatory product. Apply and reapply as per your skin condition and exosure to the sun.</p>

<p><img src="/assets/images/sunscreen.png" alt="Aloe Soothing SPF50 PA+++ Sun Cream" title="Aloe Soothing SPF50 PA+++ Sun Cream" /></p>

